thread.title: CBA profit set to pass $9b

title: CBA profit set to pass $9b
text:
Wed, Aug 12, 2015, 3:46 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 6 hrs 14 mins CBA profit set to pass $9b AAP – 14 minutes ago Print 
Commonwealth Bank is set to post another record profit, but of greater interest is how it plans to raise billions of dollars to meet new capital reserve standards. 
Analysts expect the bank to report a $9.1 billion cash profit for the 2014/15 year on Wednesday, up from $8.68 billion a year ago. 
Since ANZ tapped investors for $5.5 billion last week to meet new capital requirements imposed by the industry regulator, CBA's share price has dropped six per cent as investors expect a similar move from the nation's largest lender. 
CBA is the only one of the big four banks not to announce a capital raising in the past few months. 
Investment bank UBS estimates the lender may need to find another $10 billion or more to lift its reserves to a level the Australian Prudential Regulation Authority would be comfortable with. 
In conjunction with its earnings report, the bank could announce plans for a share placement or a change to its dividend policy in order to raise new capital.
